trans-unit.source: Specifies the default tag generated for a custom control when it is dragged from a toolbox in a tool such as Microsoft Visual Studio.
By default, the visual designer of a tool such as Visual Studio, creates an empty tag.
This is a tag representing a control in its default state, when the control is dropped from the toolbox of a visual designer onto the design surface.
To specify initial default values, a control can make use of this attribute.
You can use this attribute to customize the initial HTML content that is placed in the designer when the control is dragged from the toolbox onto the form.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.ToolboxDataAttribute"></xref> class.
The string to be set as the <xref href="System.Web.UI.ToolboxDataAttribute.Data"></xref>.
Gets the string representing the initial values of the control's property, which is used in a visual designer for creating an instance of the control.
A string representing the initial values for this attribute.
Represents the default <xref href="System.Web.UI.ToolboxDataAttribute"></xref> value for a custom control.
Tests whether the <xref href="System.Web.UI.ToolboxDataAttribute"></xref> object is equal to the given object.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.ToolboxDataAttribute.Equals%2A> method first compares the objects for equality.

If the comparison returns `false`, the <xref:System.Web.UI.ToolboxDataAttribute.Equals%2A> method then compares the data of the <xref:System.Web.UI.ToolboxDataAttribute> object to the data of the given object after first testing the given object to make sure that the given object is not `null` and is also typed as <xref:System.Web.UI.ToolboxDataAttribute> object.
The object to compare to.
`true`, if the <xref href="System.Web.UI.ToolboxDataAttribute"></xref> object is equal to the given object; otherwise, `false`.
Returns the hash code of the custom control.
A 32-bit signed `integer` representing the hash code.
Tests whether the <xref href="System.Web.UI.ToolboxDataAttribute"></xref> object contains the default value for the <xref href="System.Web.UI.ToolboxDataAttribute.Data"></xref> property.
The default is an empty string ("").
`true`, if the <xref href="System.Web.UI.ToolboxDataAttribute"></xref> contains the default value for the <xref href="System.Web.UI.ToolboxDataAttribute.Data"></xref> property; otherwise, `false`.
